			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We received a report that NaCl's logic for suspending untrusted threads on Windows (added for issue 140) can deadlock.  I've investigated this; there's definitely a bug, and I'll post a full description later.  Fixing this is complicated by the fact that SuspendThread(T) can return before thread T has actually been suspended (issue 2557).
